<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="106">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1457,770,1055]" box="[136,1457,803,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">
<keyLead box="[136,1457,803,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">1. Leaf margin at apex dentate or serrulate; leaf apex short, cuspidate; leaf margin revolute up to the base of the acumen ...............2.</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1457,770,1055]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="106">- Leaf margin at apex entire, or crenulate; leaf apex long, cuspidate to acuminate, sometimes ending in a flexuous point; leaf margin plane, reflexed in lower half of leaf, or revolute ...............................................................................................................................3.</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="106">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1457,770,1055]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="106">
2. Leaf cells at apex long, narrow, 4–6 times longer than wide; perichaetial leaves 2.0– 
<quantity box="[1037,1113,889,911]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
, about twice the size of vegetative leaves .......................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1299,1451,918,939]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hedwigiaceae" genus="Braunia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Leucodontales" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="plicata">
<emphasis box="[1299,1451,918,939]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">Braunia plicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1457,770,1055]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="106">
- Leaf cells at apex elliptical, 2–4 times longer than wide; perichaetial leaves 3.0–5.0 mm, more than 3 times the size of vegetative leaves ..................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1267,1451,975,997]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hedwigiaceae" genus="Braunia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Leucodontales" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="subincana">
<emphasis box="[1267,1451,975,997]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">Braunia subincana</emphasis>
